First thank you for removing the restriction for new accounts after I messaged you earlier. I'm working on a Passkeys plugin and the problem I wanted to report is that checkboxes don't update the store. See:

t.input({
  type: "checkbox",
  value: () => data.agreeWithTerms,
  oninput: (e) => {
    data.agreeWithTerms = e.target.value
  },
})

If I replace "checkbox" with "text" then it starts working again. I think something like v-model will be useful in pb?

Hey!

I went to open a PR, then I saw the notice in the `README.md`. So as encouraged, I'm posting here.

This is quite simple, I've been trying to use the [google_sign_in](https://pub.dev/packages/google_sign_in) package in Flutter to avoid going through the browser-based OAuth2 configuration. I ultimately got it working with this snippet:

```dart
final account = await GoogleSignIn.instance.authenticate(
  scopeHint: _googleScopes,
);

final authorization = await account.authorizationClient.authorizeServer(
  _googleScopes,
);

final code = authorization?.serverAuthCode;
if (code == null) return false;

final result = await Pb.client
    .collection('users')
    .authWithOAuth2Code('google', code, '', '');
```

However, this requires making the `redirectURL` parameter optional, else PocketBase fails before sending requests to Google, and with this method Google requires an empty value. You'll find the commit here: https://github.com/Namaneo/pocketbase/commit/e75af949fec1c306ce70077e19dd115584de20d7. Let me know if that makes sense to you, and if so I'd gladly open a PR about it if you add me as a contributor.

Thanks!
